<item>
            <title>[SEC-269] LdapAuthenticationProvider returns null userName after authentication</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-269</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Following a successful authentication from the retrieveUser method of the LdapAuthenticationProvider on the following line...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; LdapUserDetails ldapUser = authenticator.authenticate(username, password);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;... an LdapUserDetails object is always returned with a null value for the username.  Am I correct in assuming this is not the desired behaviour ?  We have our own authorities populator that requires the username so we&apos;re currently having to parse the username from the LdapUser&apos;s dn property.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cheers,&lt;br/&gt;
rob&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
